## What to do
Replace the entire contents of `src/app/globals.css` with the exact design token system from hypercerts-scaffold-atproto. Copy the file EXACTLY from `/Users/david/Projects/gainforest/hypercerts-scaffold-atproto/app/globals.css` — every @theme inline token, every :root variable, every .dark variable, every animation, .glass-panel, .noise-bg, .gradient-mesh, .stepper-line, and @layer base.

The ONLY change from the source: keep the existing scrollbar styles from identitylink at the end of the file (lines below). Append them after all the hypercerts content:

```css
/* ─── Scrollbar Styles ─── */
.overflow-y-auto {
  scrollbar-width: thin;
  scrollbar-color: oklch(0.91 0.005 260) transparent;
}
.overflow-y-auto::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 5px; }
.overflow-y-auto::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: transparent; }
.overflow-y-auto::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background-color: oklch(0.91 0.005 260); border-radius: 3px; }
.dark .overflow-y-auto { scrollbar-color: oklch(0.35 0.01 260) transparent; }
.dark .overflow-y-auto::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background-color: oklch(0.35 0.01 260); }
.scrollbar-none { -ms-overflow-style: none; scrollbar-width: none; }
.scrollbar-none::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
```

Note the scrollbar colors were updated from hex zinc to OKLCH to match the new token system.

## Do not
- Remove the `@import "tailwindcss"` directive
- Change the dark mode variant syntax (use `&:is(.dark *)` — the hypercerts version — NOT `&:where(.dark, .dark *)`)
- Add any tokens that are not in the hypercerts source file
- Remove the scrollbar utilities (just convert colors to OKLCH)
